Please check your receipt after you pay. I paid $5.29 for a breakfast sandwich that clearly states $3.99 on the menu board. When I asked why is there a $1.30 difference, the server said “I don’t make the prices, I just work here.” When I asked to speak with a manager, she said “I am the manager.” After a brief discussion she handed me back $1.00, and said “it’s not a big deal.” In short, I paid $4.86 for a $3.99 breakfast sandwich. Effective tax rate of 17.9%. On the contrary server/manager lady, it is a big deal when I pay more money than I should for sub-standard breakfast sandwich.
